name: Cocktail Notes, Vol. 1 (CN-1)
description: Introducing COCKTAIL NOTES—a new series of coasters guaranteed to make boozing even more fun. These letterpress-printed coasters look like classic cocktail napkins, but with a twist: they each feature a unique, handwritten one-liner from humor writer/international man of mystery S.H. Carlyle. The nitty-gritty: • 4.5” x 4.5” • 10 assorted coasters per set (each coaster features a different note) • Letterpress-printed on thick, 100% recycled coaster stock • Available in three equally funny volumes—collect ‘em all! Notes included in Vol. 1: • When someone says they smell something funny, they are rarely laughing. • Dear fruit-on-the-bottom yogurt: Get your shit together and stop making me do your job for you. • I just reinvented the wheel. It’s like a regular wheel except it’s covered in glitter. • No, drunk girls, it’s NOT so weird. • In space, no one can hear you crying in shower. • Plus five more! About the author: S.H. Carlyle is a humor writer whose work has been featured on McSweeney’s Internet Tendency, American Public Media’s The Dinner Party, and various other places. He has been described as “off-putting,” “creepy,” and “please just pay your bill and leave.”
